          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ConvertOverpunch6",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to convert a 6-character string representing a numeric value with an overpunch character into a standard numeric format. Overpunch characters are used in certain legacy systems to encode the sign of a number within the last digit of a numeric string. This function interprets the overpunch character and returns the corresponding numeric value."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Medium"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function involves character manipulation and conditional logic to interpret overpunch characters, which requires a moderate understanding of both SQL string functions and the overpunch encoding system. The complexity is increased by the need to handle various overpunch characters and convert them accurately."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "3. Input Parameters"
